  "text": "The factors are items contained in the critical success factors (CSFs). The CSFs consist of budget and project management, knowledge management, technology selection and adaptation, vendor relationships, information technology (IT) infrastructure, training, culture and leadership. These eight factors determine the successful implementation of social CRM and were identified by Meyliana et al. [CITATION_1] . This social CRM model examines the cause and effect relationships of CSFs in terms of the successful implementation of social CRM in the university. These causal relationships have consequences in probabilistic reasoning.",
